&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About SchoolMint:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;SchoolMint is a leading provider of K-12 Enrollment Solutions. As school choice expands and student&amp;nbsp;recruitment grows more competitive, SchoolMint will help parents, students and customers&amp;nbsp;overcome their toughest enrollment challenges.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;SchoolMint’s mission is built on our core values: No Jerks, Period; We, Not Me; Be Heroic; Bring Your Whole Self to Work; Embrace and Drive Change. These values are the foundation of our positive,&amp;nbsp;collaborative culture and commitment to exceptional customer service.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role Overview:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are a private equity–backed, SaaS company seeking a Revenue Accountant to support our finance organization. This role is highly visible and will be instrumental in the revenue accounting processes supporting operational requirements in a PE environment.&amp;nbsp; &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;The ideal candidate is comfortable operating in a fast-paced, majority offshore accounting organization, has strong technical accounting skills, and understands the importance of audit readiness, process discipline, and data integrity as the company scales toward its next value-creation milestone.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What will I do?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; Ensure revenue recognition for all subscription and professional services revenue&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; Own customer relationships for billings, collections and cash application&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; Review deferred and unbilled revenue for accuracy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; Responsible for all required sales and use tax returns, state registrations and other statutory filings&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; Review monthly revenue-related journal entries and reconciliations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; Prepare monthly commissions and partner with Human Resources on payroll&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; Partner cross-functionally with Sales and Revenue Operations teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; Support monthly close cycles and annual audit process&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; Maintain and enhance revenue accounting policies and internal controls&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About You:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; Bachelor’s degree in Accounting or Finance&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; 5 years of accounting experience, SaaS preferred&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; Experience in ASC 606 revenue recognition standards and their application in SaaS environments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; Strong understanding of subscription business models, multi-element arrangements, and professional services revenue&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; Experience with deferred revenue calculations, contract modifications, and revenue allocation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; Experience with sales and use tax filing using Avalara&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; Proficiency with Intacct and Salesforce&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; Advanced Excel skills including complex formulas, pivot tables, and financial modeling&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; CPA preferred&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; Exceptional attention to detail and accuracy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; Experience in PE-backed or high-growth environments&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; CST or EST Time Zones preferred&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
